text: Ian Graham (born 12 February 1967) is a former professional snooker player. Graham reached the final stages of the 1991 World Snooker Championship losing 3–10 to eventual semi-finalist, Steve James. In 1989, he reached the quarter- final of the Hong Kong Open, and in 1991, the quarter-final of the Grand Prix. ==References== * Category:English snooker players Category:Living people Category:1967 births
